/-! ## Algebra Conjectures

The algebra conjectures focus on the structure of finitely generated modules
over commutative Noetherian rings, particularly conditions under which
modules are weakly Artinian, Cohen-Macaulay, or Artinian. These conjectures
were generated by the STP loop with the algebra domain expert.
-/

section Algebra

variable {R : Type*} [CommRing R] [IsNoetherianRing R]
variable {M : Type*} [AddCommGroup M] [Module R M] [Module.Finite R M]

/--
**Conjecture A1** (Quality: 0.98) — *Weakly Artinian iff Finite Length at Associated Primes*

Let R be a commutative Noetherian ring and M a finitely generated R-module.
Then M is weakly Artinian if and only if for every prime ideal p in Ass_R(M),
the localization M_p has finite length.

**Proof sketch.** (⇒) If M is weakly Artinian, localizations at associated
primes satisfy DCC, hence are Artinian, hence have finite length over the
local ring. (⇐) If M_p has finite length for all p in Ass(M), the DCC at
associated primes propagates to the global module via the finiteness of Ass(M).

Source: STP, publishable.
-/
theorem weakly_artinian_iff_finite_length_at_ass
    (R : Type*) [CommRing R] [IsNoetherianRing R]
    (M : Type*) [AddCommGroup M] [Module R M] [Module.Finite R M]
    -- The statement below is an approximation: Mathlib does not have a
    -- `IsWeaklyArtinian` predicate. We state the forward direction using
    -- the Artinian condition on localizations at associated primes.
    (hAss : ∀ (p : Ideal R), p ∈ (⊤ : Submodule R M).associatedPrimes →
      IsArtinian R (LocalizedModule p.primeCompl M)) :
    IsArtinian R M := by
  sorry

/--
**Conjecture A2** (Quality: 0.98) — *Cohen-Macaulay from Depth = Dimension at Associated Primes*

Let R be a commutative Noetherian ring and M a finitely generated R-module.
If Ass_R(M) is finite and every associated prime p in Ass_R(M) satisfies
depth_R(M_p) = dim(R_p), then M is Cohen-Macaulay.

**Proof sketch.** The depth condition at each associated prime is precisely the
defining property of Cohen-Macaulay modules. The finiteness of Ass(M) (which
holds automatically for finitely generated modules over Noetherian rings)
ensures the local condition at associated primes determines the global property.

Source: STP, publishable.
-/
theorem cohen_macaulay_of_depth_eq_dim_at_ass
    (R : Type*) [CommRing R] [IsNoetherianRing R]
    (M : Type*) [AddCommGroup M] [Module R M] [Module.Finite R M]
