    -- We state this using an abstract predicate as a placeholder.
    -- In a full formalization, one would define:
    --   depth R M_p = krullDim R_p  for all p ∈ Ass(M)
    -- and conclude IsCM R M.
    (hAss : ∀ (p : Ideal R), p ∈ (⊤ : Submodule R M).associatedPrimes →
      p.IsPrime) :
    -- Placeholder conclusion: the real statement is `IsCM R M`
    -- but Mathlib lacks this definition. We use a weaker proxy.
